The paper discusses the optimization of spiking neural networks for neuromorphic applications, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the conversion of pre-trained CNNs to spiking CNNs, which involves computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the accuracy of the spiking networks, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper proposes an optimization strategy for training spiking networks, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the energy consumption of spiking networks, which falls under the category of control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
